<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport"
        content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no">
    <title>Quiz</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
        integrity="sha384-KK94CHFLLe+nY2dmCWGMq91rCGa5gtU4mk92HdvYe+M/SXH301p5ILy+dN9+nJOZ" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles/quiz.css">

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Acme&family=Montserrat:wght@100&family=Poppins:ital,wght@1,300&family=Roboto+Mono&family=Roboto:wght@100;400&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body class="container-fluid">
    <%- include("./partials/header"); %>
        <main class="container">
            <div id="container1">
                <div id="rules">
                    <ol>
                        <h1 class="display-6">Rules</h1>
                        <li>If you select the correct answer, the Selected Option indicator will turn green, and if you select the wrong answer, the selected option indicator will turn red and the correct answer indicator will turn green.</li>
                        <li>The quiz may include multiple-choice, true/false and students
                            should
                            answer each question to the best of their knowledge.</li>
                        <li>The quiz may be used as a tool for self-assessment, and students should use the results to
                            identify areas where they need to improve their knowledge or understanding.</li>
                        <li>Each question will present a scenario involving a titration, including the identity of the
                            titrant and analyte, the volumes and concentrations of the solutions used, and the endpoint
                            indicator employed.</li>
                        <li>Questions may require the student to calculate the concentration of the unknown solution,
                            the
                            volume of solution required to reach the endpoint, or other related values.</li>
                        <li>The student must understand and be able to apply the concepts of molarity, and titration to
                            solve problems related to acid-base, oxidation-reduction reactions.</li>
                        <li>The student must demonstrate an understanding of the significance of the equivalence point
                            and
                            the importance of reaching it precisely in a titration.</li>
                        <li>The quiz may include multiple-choice or calculation-based questions, and the student should
                            be
                            prepared to use the appropriate method to answer each question.</li>
                        <li>The student must be familiar with common laboratory equipment used in titrations, such as
                            burettes, pipettes, and volumetric flasks, and be able to use them accurately and precisely.
                        </li>
                        <li>The student should review and be familiar with the types of titrations used in different
                            applications, such as in the analysis of environmental samples, pharmaceuticals, and food
                            products.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <div id="start">
                        <button type="button" class="butn   " onclick="startQuiz()">Start Quiz</button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="quizes" style="display:none;">
                    <div class="container">
                        <div id="quiz" class="hidden">
                            <div id="nav">
                                <p id="progressText"></p>
                                <p id="score">Score 0</p>
                                <div id="NextBtn">
                                    <button id="btnn" id="btn" class="btn">Next Question</button>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div id="mcq">
                                <div id="q-container">
                                    <h3 class="display-6">Question</h3>
                                    <h2 id="question">Hi, what are you doing?</h2>
                                </div>
                                <div class="op">
                                    <div class="options" id="option-1">
                                        <p class="option-id">A</p>
                                        <p class="choice-text" data-id="A">Option A</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="options" id="option-2">
                                        <p class="option-id">B</p>
                                        <p class="choice-text" data-id="B">Option B</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="options" id="option-3">
                                        <p class="option-id">C</p>
                                        <p class="choice-text" data-id="C">Option C</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="options" id="option-4">
                                        <p class="option-id">D</p>
                                        <p class="choice-text" data-id="D">Option D</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <%- include("./partials/footer.ejs") %>
        </main>
</body>


<script src="./scripts/quiz.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
    integrity="sha384-ENjdO4Dr2bkBIFxQpeoTz1HIcje39Wm4jDKdf19U8gI4ddQ3GYNS7NTKfAdVQSZe"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

</html>